
A. deploy hadoop image to 1 namenode and 2 datanode

Prepare CLZ image and basic information
    namenode image download http://ppt.cc/Do-K
    root/Seethae7 // root, system administrator
    hdadm/Thoo8Xio // hdadm, hadoop user


namenode (2 network device, one for wan, another for lan)

    0. boot from iso file and restore from name node image
    1. edit /etc/network/interfaces to ponfig ip address of eth0 for wan
    2. edit /etc/network/interfaces to config another ip address 172.16.11.254
    3. echo "namenode" > /etc/hostname //set hostname to namenode

datanode-100

    0. boot from iso file and restore from name node image and boot
    1. echo "" > /usr/local/hadoop/etc/hadoop/slaves
    2. config ip address to 172.16.11.100
    3. echo "datanode100" > /etc/hostname //set hostname to datanode100

datanode-101

    0. boot from iso file and restore from name node image and boot
    1. echo "" > /usr/local/hadoop/etc/hadoop/slaves
    2. config ip address to 172.16.11.101
    3. echo "datanode101" > /etc/hostname //set hostname to datanode100


B. after deploy

First Time

    login namenode with hdadm
    mkdir /home/hdadm/namenode
    ssh datanode101; exit // fingerprint, yes
    ssh datanode102; exit
    hadoop namenode -format

Related Service start, stop, and status

    Start
	start-dfs.sh; start-yarn.sh

    Stop
	stop-yarn.sh; stop-dfs.sh
    Status
	jps
	ssh datanode100 jps
	ssh datanode101 jps

    correct status
	jps
	2663 NameNode
	2997 ResourceManager
	3440 Jps
	2842 SecondaryNameNode
	
	ssh datanode100 jps
	2336 DataNode
	2597 Jps
	2434 NodeManager
	
	ssh datanode101 jps
	2284 DataNode
	2382 NodeManager
	2502 Jps

